				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Colonial Campaigns: The Zulu War, 1879" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>From the back of the book:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Zulu War, 1879 features 11 action-packed historical scenarios from the British conquest of Zululand. Staunch British Redcoats, Colonial Cavalry, The Naval Brigade, Lancers, Highlanders and a host of Zulu warriors battle for the survival of one of Africa's premier native states.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The scenarios:&amp;#10;1. Sihayo's Kraal - January, 1879&amp;#10;2. Isandlwana - January 22, 1879&amp;#10;3. Rorke's Drift - January 22, 1879&amp;#10;4. The Battle of iNyezane River - January 22, 1879&amp;#10;5. The Battle of iNtombi Drift - March 12, 1879&amp;#10;6. Hlobane - March 28, 1879&amp;#10;7. The Battle of Khambula - March 29, 1879&amp;#10;8. Gingindhlovu - April 2, 1879&amp;#10;9. The 17th Lancers at Zungeni - June 5, 1879&amp;#10;10. Across the White Mfolozi - July 3, 1879&amp;#10;11. Last Stand at Ulundi - July 4th, 1879&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The scenarios are all organized to be played using The Sword and the Flame, but can easily be adapted to any rules set. Units are set at 8 figures instead of the traditional 20. This allows for faster play, greater flexibility and .. your 20-figure unit becomes 2&amp;frac12; units instantly! Play is on a 4' x 6' table. Give it a try!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Other sections include:&amp;#10;- History of the Zulu War&amp;#10;- Information on the British and Zulu Armies&amp;#10;- Bibliography&amp;#10;- Revised Sword and the Flame charts&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
